text: Nasry Juan Asfura Zablah (born 8 June 1958), also known as Tito Asfura, is a Honduran politician. He served as a deputy of the National Congress of Honduras. He was mayor of his nation's capital of Tegucigalpa from 2014 to 2022. He unsuccessfully ran for President of Honduras in the 2021 election. ==References== Category:1958 births Category:Living people Category:Honduran politicians Category:Mayors
